00:25:06,130 --> 00:25:08,620
No, I mean...

251
00:25:09,250 --> 00:25:13,550
That's right.
I'm that kind of bastard, aren't I?

252
00:25:14,950 --> 00:25:16,250
Let's go.

253
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:30,110
[Oppa, what are you doing?]

254
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:59,940
As you can see there is no doubt.

255
00:26:00,030 --> 00:26:04,719
<i>There is no difference in his brain scan
compared to an unhealthy one.</i>

256
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:08,089
So there really is no hope?

257
00:26:08,090 --> 00:26:13,280
Until the guardians realize
there is nothing to wait for...

258
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:47,889
My Ji Hyun... Won't you shut up?

259
00:26:47,890 --> 00:26:51,520
Why are you doing this?
Can't you hear yourself?

260
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:54,839
Why are you being so stubborn? Listen to me!

261
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:58,900
It's my life! Why should I listen to you?

262
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:01,120
Shut your mouth!

263
00:27:01,700 --> 00:27:03,780
<i>Hey, Il Shik.</i>

264
00:27:04,620 --> 00:27:06,219
Hey, Il Shik.

265
00:27:06,220 --> 00:27:09,220
Go, go, go.

266
00:27:14,550 --> 00:27:15,989
Why did you come?

267
00:27:15,990 --> 00:27:19,770
Father, let's go have dinner.

268
00:27:26,130 --> 00:27:28,020
What do you have to say?

269
00:27:28,580 --> 00:27:30,149
After you eat.

270
00:27:30,150 --> 00:27:33,480
We can eat after we talk.
I don't have an appetite.

271
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:36,030
Is there an issue at work?

272
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:43,430
That day, the contract didn't happen.

273
00:27:44,710 --> 00:27:46,480
What are you saying?

274
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:56,980
That day, Ji Hyun brought us the wrong seal.

275
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:02,370
She brought you this?

276
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:05,480
Ji Hyun didn't realize until later.

277
00:28:05,710 --> 00:28:08,750
She was bringing the seal
when she got in the accident.

278
00:28:08,860 --> 00:28:12,729
And we haven't seen the seal since.

279
00:28:12,730 --> 00:28:13,970
What?

280
00:28:14,690 --> 00:28:16,979
Why did you wait so long to tell me?

281
00:28:16,980 --> 00:28:18,430
So why did you not say anything,
all this time?

282
00:28:18,570 --> 00:28:21,079
You told me it was all settled well!

283
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:24,369
With you like this, I couldn't tell you.

284
00:28:24,370 --> 00:28:26,639
I wanted to try everything else first...

285
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:30,260
Even so! This is so unlike you.

286
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:38,830
Yes, I am like this right now.

287
00:28:40,300 --> 00:28:47,230
They are still waiting on the contract
but to sell the land without the seal...

288
00:28:47,950 --> 00:28:53,620
we must... declare Ji Hyun dead.

289
00:28:56,540 --> 00:28:58,340
Declare her dead?

290
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:02,440
I can't do it, Father.

291
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:05,459
I can't do it.

292
00:29:05,460 --> 00:29:07,590
I have no confidence to do that,
I do not have the self-confidence to do it.

293
00:29:08,470 --> 00:29:13,400
Since it is Father's company...
please take care of it.

294
00:29:14,270 --> 00:29:20,930
I would just like to be by Ji Hyun's side.

295
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:27,950
[Letter of Resignation]

296
00:29:47,090 --> 00:29:49,609
Is today your wedding anniversary?

297
00:29:49,610 --> 00:29:53,699
My husband wouldn't make me clean
on our wedding anniversary.

298
00:29:53,700 --> 00:29:56,189
Once a month, they make a special day.

299
00:29:56,190 --> 00:29:59,019
My Hwa Jun usually devours pasta,
bread, and things,

300
00:29:59,020 --> 00:30:01,789
but for my health
we've only eaten Korean food.

301
00:30:01,790 --> 00:30:08,690
So once a month,
on cleaning day he cooks me pasta.

302
00:30:09,030 --> 00:30:13,309
I see... but can we butt in and eat too?

303
00:30:13,310 --> 00:30:16,679
Not a chance. You two please eat over there.

304
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:19,279
The pasta will be overcooked, please eat.

305
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:22,670
Your food is in the kitchen.

306
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:29,380
Kang, would you turn off the lights?

307
00:30:40,950 --> 00:30:42,990
Here, let�s toast.

308
00:31:02,010 --> 00:31:04,190
<i>I don't like basil leaves.</i>

309
00:31:18,270 --> 00:31:19,970
Here.

310
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:29,199
Ahjussi and ahjumma
must really love each other.

311
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,839
Who fakes love?

312
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:32,580
I'm jealous.

313
00:31:33,290 --> 00:31:36,200
I wanted to live like that.

314
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:54,379
Women are so simple.

315
00:31:54,380 --> 00:31:57,989
He just wanted her to clean all day.

316
00:31:57,990 --> 00:32:01,910
To call that comforting...
men are so stupid.

317
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:04,959
You just said that to comfort me.

318
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:05,879
What? Why would I?

319
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:08,090
You're saying he's manipulating her?

320
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:09,959
I better ask him.

321
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:12,239
Why are you doing this?

322
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:15,190
I didn't know.
You're quite a coward, aren't you?

323
00:32:15,970 --> 00:32:17,900
Are you making fun of me?

324
00:32:23,430 --> 00:32:24,940
Hey, stop.

325
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:29,820
Take this...
it includes up to yesterday's pay.

326
00:32:31,100 --> 00:32:32,259
It's money!

327
00:32:32,260 --> 00:32:34,079
Good, I had spent everything.

328
00:32:34,080 --> 00:32:35,780
I'm saved.

329
00:32:36,210 --> 00:32:39,400
I put in cab fare as well,
so take a taxi home.

330
00:32:40,590 --> 00:32:43,320
Because you helped clean.

331
00:32:46,020 --> 00:32:49,899
If I help out even when I'm not asked,
will you give me more money?

332
00:32:49,900 --> 00:32:51,190
What?

333
00:32:51,510 --> 00:32:54,740
Thank you, Han Kang.

334
00:32:55,370 --> 00:32:57,010
I'll see you tomorrow.

335
00:33:00,540 --> 00:33:04,230
She's not normal, I can't read her.

336
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:15,000
<i>The tears keep coming.</i>

337
00:33:15,420 --> 00:33:21,300
<i>No one will cry for me,
but I'm crying for myself.</i>

338
00:33:22,650 --> 00:33:30,200
<i>I wish I had just one person to count on,
on a day like today.</i>

339
00:33:30,750 --> 00:33:33,990
<i>Just one person.</i>

340
00:33:34,620 --> 00:33:37,330
<i>Ahh, my body cringes!</i>

341
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:43,809
<i>Thou for someone to just shed a tear.</i>

342
00:33:43,810 --> 00:33:46,709
Are these words fit for 2010?

343
00:33:46,710 --> 00:33:50,969
Those are words from Old Korea...
[Scheduler]

344
00:33:50,970 --> 00:33:54,489
and so immature coming from an 80s cartoon
character with uncontrollable feelings!

345
00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:56,819
Is that really what you should be
worrying about?

346
00:33:56,820 --> 00:34:00,080
Is it time right now to be
looking for one person?

347
00:34:02,930 --> 00:34:04,240
Hey!

348
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:13,129
You were saying that to me, weren't you?

349
00:34:13,490 --> 00:34:17,469
"Cringing, immature romantic cartoon
character, with uncontrollable feelings"!

350
00:34:17,470 --> 00:34:21,500
Noona, I was just on Twitter.

351
00:34:22,030 --> 00:34:23,039
Twitter?

352
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:26,140
What are you doing here?

353
00:34:26,470 --> 00:34:29,229
This is the way home.

354
00:34:29,230 --> 00:34:30,699
Why are you going home?

355
00:34:30,700 --> 00:34:33,259
You said you'd stake your life on
getting vengeance for the betrayal.

356
00:34:33,260 --> 00:34:36,500
Why aren't you impressively set to
auto-destruct and whining instead?

357
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:38,580
Oh, that.

358
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:42,039
I did that. I found the seal!

359
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:44,619
Mm, you used your brain, eh?

360
00:34:44,620 --> 00:34:48,779
It was very strange. While I lived as
Shin Ji Hyun, my memory wasn't very good,

361
00:34:48,780 --> 00:34:51,819
but ever since I became like this
my memory is perfect!

362
00:34:51,820 --> 00:34:53,259
That's enough.

363
00:34:53,260 --> 00:34:56,219
Then I too, will cancel
the emergency measure status.

364
00:34:56,220 --> 00:35:00,210
Were you on standby because of me? Sorry.

365
00:35:16,780 --> 00:35:19,950
Because of you I missed
the Jupuhlgae brother�s concert.

366
00:35:21,270 --> 00:35:23,660
I guess I should go to a Hongdae club.

367
00:35:24,600 --> 00:35:25,930
Bye.

368
00:35:27,470 --> 00:35:30,740
Today was originally my wedding day.

369
00:35:37,420 --> 00:35:45,240
It's my wedding day, but I thwarted my
husband-to-be and jumped for joy.

370
00:35:45,730 --> 00:35:47,600
Ridiculous, huh?

371
00:35:48,770 --> 00:35:51,160
This life is usually some sort of comedy.

372
00:35:51,240 --> 00:35:53,240
There's a lot of that in this neighborhood.

373
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:56,420
You said I was the third.

374
00:35:56,730 --> 00:35:58,079
What are you talking about?

375
00:35:58,080 --> 00:36:07,250
Your 49 day journeyers... one chose to die,
what happened to the other?

376
00:36:07,930 --> 00:36:10,400
Where did that come from?

377
00:36:12,010 --> 00:36:13,769
My mistake...

378
00:36:13,770 --> 00:36:16,009
Did I say you made a mistake?

379
00:36:16,010 --> 00:36:17,579
Then did he live?

380
00:36:17,580 --> 00:36:19,359
Did he find the three drops of tears?

381
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:23,029
Did that person have 3 people
who truly loved him?

382
00:36:23,030 --> 00:36:25,080
It's a precious secret not to be divulged.

383
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:30,809
Why not just tell me?

384
00:36:30,810 --> 00:36:32,379
If I say he failed, will you quit?

385
00:36:32,380 --> 00:36:34,910
And if he succeeded, you'll cheer?

386
00:36:34,930 --> 00:36:36,329
Who says I'll quit?

387
00:36:36,330 --> 00:36:39,239
In the time you're wondering
whether someone else lived or died,

388
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:41,590
work on finding your own tears.

389
00:36:42,130 --> 00:36:47,600
You've got 35 minutes
before you're late. Go home!

390
00:36:48,020 --> 00:36:49,990
Okay.

391
00:37:00,700 --> 00:37:02,519
[Letter of Resignation]

392
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:07,800
You're still breathing...

393
00:37:12,350 --> 00:37:15,550
...and your hands are warm...

394
00:37:19,380 --> 00:37:22,440
but I need to declare your death.

395
00:37:32,350 --> 00:37:38,120
So, now that I've hidden my seal,
they won't be able to sell my land.

396
00:37:38,900 --> 00:37:43,260
And if they can't sell my land, they won't
have the money to fund the business.

397
00:37:43,610 --> 00:37:49,640
Then my father will get involved
and then find out the whole thing.

398
00:37:53,960 --> 00:38:00,410
Now I need to find a way to live on,
but my future looks gloomy.

399
00:38:13,090 --> 00:38:15,540
[Congrats! You have 43 days left.
The Scheduler.]

400
00:38:32,270 --> 00:38:35,429
If you wanted to see me, you should have
come in and brought me out.

401
00:38:35,430 --> 00:38:37,819
<i>Must you make me wait
until that girl comes out?</i>

402
00:38:37,820 --> 00:38:40,589
I told you, I don't like going in that room.

403
00:38:40,590 --> 00:38:43,600
- Why?
- I don't know, I just don't like it.

404
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:47,610
- Get on.
- Where are we going?

405
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:53,450
Why are we here?

406
00:39:10,650 --> 00:39:11,930
Pick.

407
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:13,439
What?

408
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:16,410
Pick some clothes you like.

409
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:21,100
Isn't shopping the number one cure
for women's melancholy?

410
00:39:21,260 --> 00:39:23,550
I'm not in the mood.

411
00:39:31,930 --> 00:39:33,599
Hey! What is this!

412
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:37,039
Congratulatory present.
Today was your wedding day, right?

413
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:41,040
Congratulations on the failure or
congratulations on the success?

414
00:39:41,210 --> 00:39:43,280
You want to die?

415
00:39:52,130 --> 00:39:55,199
Pervert!
Won't you take this off immediately?

416
00:39:55,200 --> 00:40:00,720
Really? Top, bottom, everything?

417
00:40:02,190 --> 00:40:05,289
Take it all off and I'll really kill you!

418
00:40:05,290 --> 00:40:09,189
Unni, I'm already dead.

419
00:40:09,190 --> 00:40:11,310
You that unsure of yourself?

420
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:13,780
Didn't take care of your body, did you?

421
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:20,360
You're too much. Can you really do this
on this kind of day?

422
00:40:20,580 --> 00:40:22,450
What kind of day is it?

423
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:29,250
Not getting married to Kang Min Ho was the
best thing that ever happened in your life.

424
00:40:29,610 --> 00:40:34,140
Is it something to cry and whine about
or celebrate and shop about?

425
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:36,259
That's true.

426
00:40:36,260 --> 00:40:39,759
Yes, it is. So, choose, choose.

427
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:41,750
Shall we start again?

428
00:40:42,320 --> 00:40:43,720
Sounds good.

429
00:41:35,590 --> 00:41:39,989
Once-living women carry the smell of
dwenjang* even into death. [*soybean paste]

430
00:41:39,990 --> 00:41:44,140
Buy some clothes, do your hair
and suddenly you're all happy.

431
00:41:44,410 --> 00:41:46,850
That's not why.

432
00:41:49,580 --> 00:41:53,160
Yes, it is. Before.

433
00:41:56,240 --> 00:41:57,850
After.

434
00:41:59,730 --> 00:42:03,990
There are still two on my side...
I'm happy about that.

435
00:42:04,020 --> 00:42:05,280
Two?

436
00:42:05,490 --> 00:42:07,220
You and Han Kang.

437
00:42:07,610 --> 00:42:11,639
Han Kang is more on Song Yi Kyung's side
rather than mine, but still.

438
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:18,059
I'm not on your side either.
I'm the Scheduler of a million people.

439
00:42:18,060 --> 00:42:19,650
It's strange.

440
00:42:19,730 --> 00:42:25,859
The one I trusted most in the world, Min Ho,
is actually an incredibly scary person.

441
00:42:25,860 --> 00:42:31,450
And the most distant and strict Han Kang
is true and warm.

442
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:36,170
How can people seem so different?

443
00:42:37,340 --> 00:42:39,669
Didn't you know that most people
are like that?

444
00:42:39,670 --> 00:42:41,880
How have you been living?

445
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:45,549
No kidding, how have I been living 'til now?

446
00:42:45,550 --> 00:42:48,349
Stop. That's enough.

447
00:42:48,350 --> 00:42:50,740
You think I'm your friend?

448
00:42:50,990 --> 00:42:54,960
Now that we're done, let's go our own way.

449
00:42:56,630 --> 00:42:58,980
Hey. What about me?

450
00:42:59,160 --> 00:43:01,989
The buses aren't running yet.

451
00:43:01,990 --> 00:43:05,230
I'll take you home just this once.

452
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:08,779
I don't want to go home.

453
00:43:08,780 --> 00:43:11,910
I don't want to wait in a hole
for unni to come back.

454
00:43:13,570 --> 00:43:18,140
Are you saying
we should find a room together?

455
00:43:19,220 --> 00:43:20,950
Are you crazy?

456
00:43:33,290 --> 00:43:38,860
Ji Hyun always loved
my rolled egg side dish the most.

457
00:43:43,550 --> 00:43:46,920
Eat it for her, please.

458
00:43:48,150 --> 00:43:50,670
If she hadn't gotten in the accident,

459
00:43:50,680 --> 00:43:55,200
by this time she would have called us
about her wedding night, no?

460
00:43:56,550 --> 00:43:58,140
Let's eat.

461
00:43:59,970 --> 00:44:03,089
Why would she have gone to show Min Ho
the bridesmaid's dress?!

462
00:44:03,090 --> 00:44:05,829
It wasn't her wedding dress.
That was for us to wear!

463
00:44:05,830 --> 00:44:07,730
Stop it.

464
00:44:07,760 --> 00:44:10,190
Why are you getting angry?

465
00:44:11,900 --> 00:44:13,609
Hey, Shin In Jung.

466
00:44:13,610 --> 00:44:17,779
After Ji Hyun's accident,
I've been going crazy, too.

467
00:44:17,780 --> 00:44:21,250
But because of you I didn't even
have a chance to cry in peace.

468
00:44:24,350 --> 00:44:28,430
Hey, are you her only friend?! I am too!

469
00:44:50,840 --> 00:44:53,739
Why are you like this?
Haven't you been sleeping during the day?

470
00:44:53,740 --> 00:44:55,489
I'm sorry.

471
00:44:55,490 --> 00:44:58,980
You've been so tired because of me...

472
00:45:03,160 --> 00:45:07,750
Yi Kyung, I almost missed you.

473
00:45:08,410 --> 00:45:10,940
Unni, you have a boyfriend?

474
00:45:11,150 --> 00:45:14,960
Let's have a bowl of hwejang soup.
There's a good place just down here.

475
00:45:21,870 --> 00:45:25,620
I went through all of that.
Don't you owe me a meal at least?

476
00:45:32,020 --> 00:45:35,100
I'm not asking for the meal itself.

477
00:45:38,710 --> 00:45:44,420
I... it was my fault that
that person died, 100%.

478
00:45:44,980 --> 00:45:49,999
I left the hospital and hid for two years
in a quiet place without people.

479
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:55,399
I lived like a dead man for two years.
But after two years, I woke up.

480
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:57,419
Just as I decided to leave this world,

481
00:45:57,420 --> 00:46:01,980
I saw you in the convenience store
six months ago and I couldn't go.

482
00:46:02,570 --> 00:46:08,640
It's been five years for you. Living like
this for five years... you can't do that.

483
00:46:09,280 --> 00:46:10,589
So what?

484
00:46:10,590 --> 00:46:13,219
Bring out everything you've bottled up.

485
00:46:13,220 --> 00:46:14,979
I'll help.

486
00:46:14,980 --> 00:46:18,570
I can now listen to you properly.

487
00:46:22,850 --> 00:46:26,959
I don't like a doctor
who knows of that time.

488
00:46:26,960 --> 00:46:31,530
I don't need your help.

489
00:46:33,060 --> 00:46:36,240
Please don't do this.
You need to let it out.

490
00:46:36,380 --> 00:46:40,000
I will be your friend.

491
00:46:45,350 --> 00:46:49,210
Be my what? Friend?

492
00:46:53,410 --> 00:46:57,780
It doesn't matter who is in this world,
it doesn't matter.

493
00:46:58,060 --> 00:47:01,660
I don't need anyone.

494
00:47:01,720 --> 00:47:10,140
A psychiatrist or friend,
I don't need either so go your own way.

495
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:36,580
Unni, you lived like this for five years?

496
00:47:37,940 --> 00:47:40,310
Who died?

497
00:47:43,080 --> 00:47:49,290
Did your whole family die at once?

498
00:48:04,720 --> 00:48:07,410
What if my parents are like this?

499
00:48:10,820 --> 00:48:22,040
If something happens to me...
my parents would live like this, unni.

500
00:48:24,120 --> 00:48:26,400
That can't happen.

501
00:48:34,100 --> 00:48:36,230
How many days are left?

502
00:48:37,090 --> 00:48:41,580
<i>41 days 3 hours 29 minutes left.</i>

503
00:48:53,070 --> 00:48:56,090
Just seeing you like this helps.

504
00:48:59,060 --> 00:49:04,260
<i>Just wait, Mom and Dad.
No matter what it takes, I'll come back.</i>

505
00:49:11,250 --> 00:49:13,510
[Seoul Middle School
Oh Myung Suh, Yoo Kyung Ee, Cho Sun Soo]

506
00:49:15,250 --> 00:49:16,970
Who else is there?

507
00:49:20,260 --> 00:49:24,260
Park Seo Woo, Han Kang

508
00:49:25,550 --> 00:49:28,659
Between these, who will I run into first?

509
00:49:28,660 --> 00:49:32,020
Choose an order and...

510
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:40,280
Phone number. All the phone numbers
are in my old hand phone...

511
00:49:56,240 --> 00:49:59,920
I'm not late, right? I ran the whole way.

512
00:50:01,380 --> 00:50:05,039
But, can I use the computer?

513
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:07,960
You're here five minutes early
and you want to use the computer?

514
00:50:08,240 --> 00:50:12,550
That's true. What about at lunch and breaks?

515
00:50:13,160 --> 00:50:14,680
Go ahead and use it.

516
00:50:18,910 --> 00:50:21,430
Acting close.

517
00:50:32,980 --> 00:50:34,830
[College Friends
Yoon Jae Sun, Kim Joo Ri, Park Woo Sung]

518
00:50:45,490 --> 00:50:46,709
[Club members, Park Jung Eun]

519
00:50:46,710 --> 00:50:50,090
Even meeting one a day,
how long will it take?

520
00:50:53,170 --> 00:50:58,750
But I work from 11 to 11,
when can I meet them?

521
00:51:01,570 --> 00:51:05,079
He just took the elevator.
He should be there soon.

522
00:51:05,080 --> 00:51:07,110
Good, okay

523
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:10,970
Did you make an investment?

524
00:51:11,670 --> 00:51:14,220
I'm an employee of Shin Ga San Up,

525
00:51:15,400 --> 00:51:20,820
and the president is working, why would you
bring up his daughter's accident?!

526
00:51:23,520 --> 00:51:26,850
I apologize, I'll call back soon.

527
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:34,230
Father.

528
00:51:35,950 --> 00:51:37,480
Who is it?

529
00:51:44,090 --> 00:51:45,769
What is it all of a sudden?

530
00:51:45,770 --> 00:51:51,740
- What brings you here all of a sudden?
- All of a sudden? You are a ruthless boy.

531
00:51:53,080 --> 00:51:56,080
You saw me as a meaningless father.

532
00:51:56,260 --> 00:51:59,779
Ji Hyun... you can't declare her dead?

533
00:51:59,780 --> 00:52:01,259
Then what about me?

534
00:52:01,260 --> 00:52:04,620
Do you think I can declare
my own daughter dead!?

535
00:52:04,970 --> 00:52:06,650
I'm sorry.

536
00:52:06,980 --> 00:52:08,760
But the company...

537
00:52:09,880 --> 00:52:15,749
As you know, without Ji Hyun�s land,
there's no way we can get the money.

538
00:52:15,750 --> 00:52:17,740
Find another way.

539
00:52:19,260 --> 00:52:20,890
You find it.

540
00:52:23,870 --> 00:52:26,600
I didn't make the choice that easily.

541
00:52:27,220 --> 00:52:29,339
I can't concentrate on the company.

542
00:52:29,340 --> 00:52:31,870
Don't you care what happens to the company?

543
00:52:32,320 --> 00:52:34,159
What will you do not working here?

544
00:52:34,160 --> 00:52:36,809
This company belongs to you.

545
00:52:36,810 --> 00:52:40,119
I will take care of Ji Hyun,
so you can take care of the company.

546
00:52:40,120 --> 00:52:42,780
Quit the company and watch over Ji Hyun!?

547
00:52:43,330 --> 00:52:45,230
You call yourself a man?

548
00:52:45,640 --> 00:52:49,960
If you're like this and my daughter wakes
up, you think I'd still give her to you?

549
00:52:50,070 --> 00:52:52,959
To a weak-willed bum who quit his job?

550
00:52:52,960 --> 00:52:57,579
Even if it isn't your company,
I can still support Ji Hyun.

551
00:52:57,580 --> 00:53:00,840
Immature, thick-headed...

552
00:53:00,990 --> 00:53:03,499
That's what I'm saying, you fool!

553
00:53:03,500 --> 00:53:06,139
I scouted you to this company.

554
00:53:06,140 --> 00:53:08,600
Did you come to this company
because of Ji Hyun?

555
00:53:08,840 --> 00:53:10,870
Yes, I came for Ji Hyun.

556
00:53:12,070 --> 00:53:16,079
If not for Ji Hyun
why would I have come to Shin Ga San Up?

557
00:53:16,080 --> 00:53:18,319
Because your offer was too good to refuse?

558
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:20,200
Because of the perks?

559
00:53:21,330 --> 00:53:25,700
Because I might succeed you?

560
00:53:25,720 --> 00:53:29,770
You merciless boy. You think I don't know
you're a good catch.

561
00:53:30,810 --> 00:53:34,909
You and I both know that there's a chance
Ji Hyun could be like that forever.

562
00:53:34,910 --> 00:53:38,630
So why can you and not I be by her side!

563
00:53:40,640 --> 00:53:43,810
Because you're the only person I can trust.

564
00:53:45,040 --> 00:53:52,139
After just a little time, you'll know why.

565
00:53:52,140 --> 00:53:56,870
You'll be able to understand me.

566
00:53:58,360 --> 00:54:00,789
Why are you doing this to me?

567
00:54:00,790 --> 00:54:02,750
You're still here.

568
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:07,010
Isn't this request enough?

569
00:54:07,200 --> 00:54:08,680
Father.

570
00:54:25,310 --> 00:54:27,209
<i>It's been handled well.</i>

571
00:54:27,210 --> 00:54:31,840
<i>Don't worry.
I'll call after meeting with Dr. Jung.</i>

572
00:54:36,670 --> 00:54:43,849
He chose you, Manager Kang,
who is quite skillful.

573
00:54:43,850 --> 00:54:48,740
It's not a praiseworthy task
since losing the seal was my fault.

574
00:54:49,880 --> 00:54:54,010
Then, how shall we proceed?

575
00:54:54,820 --> 00:54:58,849
So as we planned, Mr. Jung, you will support
us on the Singapore and Haemido land.

576
00:54:58,850 --> 00:55:01,350
It is like a guarantee for the contract.

577
00:55:01,450 --> 00:55:02,809
A guarantee?

578
00:55:02,810 --> 00:55:09,020
If the money is not paid back in time,
the land in Haemido becomes yours.

579
00:55:11,500 --> 00:55:15,060
If you can't pay back, Haemido is ours...

580
00:55:15,310 --> 00:55:20,860
and if you find the daughter's seal
then our plan goes back to the original.

581
00:55:21,900 --> 00:55:24,499
Contact me once you've
ironed out your terms.

582
00:55:24,500 --> 00:55:27,210
We still need the okay from President Shin.

583
00:55:29,510 --> 00:55:30,940
[Kang]

584
00:55:35,380 --> 00:55:36,910
Hello, Kang.

585
00:55:38,370 --> 00:55:39,729
You want to meet today?

586
00:55:39,730 --> 00:55:41,019
What's this about?

587
00:55:41,020 --> 00:55:43,450
If it were something I could say
over the phone, would I ask you over?

588
00:55:44,390 --> 00:55:48,090
Okay, I'll wait.

589
00:55:53,800 --> 00:55:55,930
Why do you keep doing that?

590
00:56:01,150 --> 00:56:03,690
<i>You're meeting Kang before coming here?</i>

591
00:56:04,070 --> 00:56:07,000
You know how much
I've been worrying since yesterday.

592
00:56:07,220 --> 00:56:10,010
I'm out of my mind with curiosity.

593
00:56:10,100 --> 00:56:13,610
I'll call after hearing
what Kang has to say. Go home.

594
00:56:15,730 --> 00:56:18,080
<i>Not my house, yours.</i>

595
00:56:19,490 --> 00:56:23,640
We should still be careful. See you later.

596
00:56:38,260 --> 00:56:39,399
You called?

597
00:56:39,400 --> 00:56:41,059
The shop is really busy right now.

598
00:56:41,060 --> 00:56:43,749
Why do you make me call you
when we're really busy?

599
00:56:43,750 --> 00:56:44,489
What?

600
00:56:44,490 --> 00:56:49,780
Why do you keep poking your head in?

601
00:56:50,000 --> 00:56:50,739
You saw?

602
00:56:50,740 --> 00:56:53,040
You made me see, and now, you saw?

603
00:56:54,330 --> 00:56:59,449
What do you need now? I'm curious.

604
00:56:59,450 --> 00:57:04,519
Well, there's something
I'd like to negotiate with you.

605
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:06,129
I know I have no right to but...

606
00:57:06,130 --> 00:57:06,999
Negotiate?

607
00:57:07,000 --> 00:57:08,519
You remember what you said?

608
00:57:08,520 --> 00:57:10,019
That day I almost choked and died.

609
00:57:10,020 --> 00:57:11,019
Your words, really.

610
00:57:11,020 --> 00:57:17,070
Anyway, you said, how could I come and go
as I please as if this were a freelance job?

611
00:57:18,290 --> 00:57:19,929
Can't I do that?

612
00:57:19,930 --> 00:57:21,159
Freelance job?

613
00:57:21,160 --> 00:57:23,479
I don't have much time in this body anyway,

614
00:57:23,480 --> 00:57:29,089
and there's so much to take care of but
I don't have time outside of working here.

615
00:57:29,090 --> 00:57:31,719
Instead, I'll just take 30,000 won an hour.

616
00:57:31,720 --> 00:57:32,609
30,000?

617
00:57:32,610 --> 00:57:35,829
Honestly, 40,000 an hour
wasn't that much to start with!

618
00:57:35,830 --> 00:57:40,569
When I looked up minimum wage,
it's actually 43,200 per hour.

619
00:57:40,570 --> 00:57:43,930
Less than that, it's like slavery!

620
00:57:44,450 --> 00:57:46,319
You might as well report me.

621
00:57:46,320 --> 00:57:51,059
Oh no, of course not.

622
00:57:51,060 --> 00:57:52,239
It's not my place.

623
00:57:52,240 --> 00:57:56,040
Does someone who knows her place borrow my
computer to look up minimum wage standards?

624
00:57:56,170 --> 00:57:59,279
I didn�t borrow your computer
for that reason.

625
00:57:59,280 --> 00:58:03,149
Then how did you find out the
minimum wage?

626
00:58:03,150 --> 00:58:08,679
That was to figure out how to calculate
the freelance job rate.

627
00:58:08,680 --> 00:58:11,030
So you did do a search here.

628
00:58:11,250 --> 00:58:16,650
I did, but I really did it
for the job rate...

629
00:58:18,290 --> 00:58:23,689
Do you think someone who stiffed you 320 won
will really pay a freelance rate of 30,000?

630
00:58:23,690 --> 00:58:27,520
$2.50. Would that be enough?

631
00:58:27,600 --> 00:58:29,510
Try a little harder.

632
00:58:43,800 --> 00:58:45,599
Thank you for everything.

633
00:58:45,600 --> 00:58:48,410
I'll try to find another freelance job.

634
00:58:48,860 --> 00:58:50,270
Just a minute.

635
00:58:50,740 --> 00:58:52,850
That was a joke.

636
00:58:53,240 --> 00:58:55,419
You know my circumstances
and that was a joke?

637
00:58:55,420 --> 00:59:00,419
That... Do it, the freelance job.
Let's make the contract.

638
00:59:00,420 --> 00:59:04,120
For how much? 30,000? 40,000?
50,000? 100,000?

639
00:59:05,430 --> 00:59:11,579
What you get now.
No, 45,000 sounds good, right?

640
00:59:11,580 --> 00:59:15,410
<i>That way we have met
the minimum wage standards...</i>

641
00:59:20,740 --> 00:59:23,849
What's this? Are you making fun of me?

642
00:59:23,850 --> 00:59:26,019
No, just a joke.

643
00:59:26,020 --> 00:59:27,129
Surprised?

644
00:59:27,130 --> 00:59:29,280
You really thought I was angry, didn't you?

645
00:59:58,880 --> 01:00:02,020
<i>Did you come to drink
because you couldn't find my seal?</i>

646
01:00:10,770 --> 01:00:14,299
Gi Jun, call Song Yi Kyung over.

647
01:00:14,300 --> 01:00:15,580
Okay.

648
01:00:15,650 --> 01:00:17,290
Noonim.

649
01:00:33,570 --> 01:00:39,760
Song Yi Kyung, if you don't want to be
misunderstood, don't act so you could be.

650
01:00:40,470 --> 01:00:43,910
Like just now, why act in such a way
to be misunderstood?

651
01:00:44,090 --> 01:00:47,069
Just now, I was just standing here, sir.

652
01:00:47,070 --> 01:00:50,530
Showing no response
when a customer is speaking.

653
01:00:50,600 --> 01:00:53,889
<i>Ignoring someone after seeing them.</i>

654
01:00:53,890 --> 01:00:57,990
At first being overly friendly,
then not at all.

655
01:00:58,380 --> 01:01:00,600
This isn't right.

656
01:01:02,030 --> 01:01:03,810
I understand.

657
01:01:04,620 --> 01:01:07,240
And not apologizing
after receiving criticism?

658
01:01:09,040 --> 01:01:10,710
Won't you apologize?

659
01:01:13,190 --> 01:01:18,460
<i>Remember, if your necklace breaks,
your 49 days are over.</i>

660
01:01:25,810 --> 01:01:27,740
I'll strive to correct my behavior.

661
01:01:28,380 --> 01:01:32,350
Where did you hear I had a fiancee?

662
01:01:35,330 --> 01:01:38,420
You don't have a fiancee?

663
01:01:39,270 --> 01:01:41,729
I do, but...

664
01:01:41,730 --> 01:01:49,570
Sir, I'm at work,
I have no interest in your personal life.

665
01:01:50,700 --> 01:01:52,160
Just a moment.

666
01:01:58,780 --> 01:02:00,250
Hyung, you're here.

667
01:02:01,290 --> 01:02:03,489
You should have come to my office,
